findings.liver: Homogeneous with no focal lesion identified.
findings.gallbladder: Distended with surrounding inflammatory changes and wall edema, punctate hyperdensity within the gallbladder neck compatible with a stone.
findings.kidneys: No nephrolithiasis, bilateral cortical hypodensities, largest extending from the inferior pole of the left kidney measured 5.4 x 5.2 cm, most compatible with a simple cyst, stranding about bilateral kidneys is symmetric.
findings.abdominal aorta: Moderate atherosclerotic calcifications, infrarenal aorta aneurysmal measuring 3.5 x 2.5 cm.
findings.colon: Moderate diverticular disease without evidence of diverticulitis.
findings.pelvis: Bladder moderately distended and grossly unremarkable, prostate gland and seminal vesicles within normal limits, no pelvic free fluid.
findings.inguinal hernias: Small bilateral fat containing inguinal hernias noted.
findings.osseous structures: No suspicious lytic or blastic lesions, multilevel degenerative changes most prominent at the L4-L5 level.
